b'One Off': b"A slice of life of high school girls in the early summer. Shiozaki Haruno is a 17-year-old girl who loves her motor cycle, HONDA's Giorno. She lives in remote highlands and longs for a vivid life in a city. \n\nEncounters with people staying at Haruno's parents' boardinghouse encourage her to step forward to her dream."
